==English==

===Etymology===
From an Old French variant of [[plessier]] ‘plash’, from Proto-Romance [[plessier]], from Latin [[plectere]] ‘weave, plait’.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/pli:ʧ/}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|pleach|es}}

# {{transitive}} To unite by interweaving, as branches of trees; to [[plash]]; to [[interlock]].

[[fr:pleach]]